	</div>
</div>


## You’ll know you’re successfully doing this because:

- You are challenging your own assumptions and bias, and those in your team and stakeholders
- You have conducted desk research as part of your research, using existing insight and evidence to inform your own research plan
- You can clearly explain the rationale for your research
- You understand and can explain the risks of bias in research
- You take the time to learn what has gone well and what could be improved in your research

## How we help you to do this:

- Our department-wide research and evidence library ('RED')
- Links to other departmental data and evidence, and to academic and other third-party research sources
- Links to resources and training on bias

### In the future we also plan:

- Insight management tools in each portfolio
- Baseline insights about all common user groups in the department
- Training on research biases

